article.description: — Greg Parham had 23 points as VMI easily defeated Western Carolina 87-61 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Parham scores 23 to lift VMI over Western Carolina 87-61
article.linkText: Parham scores 23 to lift VMI over Western Carolina 87-61
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. -- — Greg Parham had 23 points as VMI easily defeated Western Carolina 87-61 on Wednesday night. Parham shot 5 for 7 from deep. He added six rebounds. Sean Conway had 14 points for VMI (9-8, 4-4 Southern Conference). Jake Stephens added 12 points, nine rebounds and four assists, and Kamdyn Curfman had 10 points. Mason Faulkner had 15 points and six rebounds for the Catamounts (7-8, 0-6), whose losing streak stretched to six games. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
